{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"fields":{"description":"## Description\nLOC/size analyzer that shells `scc --format json` (deterministic, no network) and populates `AnalyzerResult.loc` (per-file/per-language LOC + max_loc). Absent scc -> `Unavailable`, never fabricated zeros.\n\n## Approach & rationale (G6)\nExtract the EXISTING scc JSON parse from `src/rebar/grounding/engine_b_backends.py` (`_metric_invoke`/`_scc_files`) into one shared helper `rebar.metrics.analyzers._scc.parse_scc_json`, then have BOTH callers use it. Rationale: a single normalizer is lower blast-radius and avoids a second, drifting scc-JSON parser — preferred over writing a fresh parser in scc_loc.py. No novel architecture (T1): this reuses the established in-repo scc shell-out pattern; scc is a mature OSS CLI already invoked by the grounding backend.\n\n## Grounding (E4/G1G2 — verified via Grep/Read)\n- CONFIRMED: `grep -n \"\\\"--format\\\", \\\"json\\\"\" src/rebar/grounding/engine_b_backends.py` shows the existing scc JSON shell-out at :376; `_scc_files(data)` at :412 normalizes per-file LOC.\n- New files CREATED by this ticket: `src/rebar/metrics/analyzers/scc_loc.py`, `src/rebar/metrics/analyzers/_scc.py`. `AnalyzerResult`/`Unavailable(reason, accruing_since)` come from ticket 3b30 (depends_on). Consumer updated OUTSIDE this dir: `engine_b_backends.py` (re-pointed at the shared helper).\n\n## Acceptance criteria (each an observable outcome with a proving command)\n- [ ] `parse_scc_json` exists in `analyzers/_scc.py` and returns per-file LOC + max_loc. PROVE: `pytest -q tests/unit/metrics/test_scc_loc.py::test_parse_scc_json_shape`.\n- [ ] `engine_b_backends` uses the SAME parser (single normalizer). PROVE: `pytest -q tests/unit/metrics/test_scc_loc.py::test_single_parser_reused` which asserts `import rebar.grounding.engine_b_backends as g, rebar.metrics.analyzers._scc as s; assert g._scc_files.__module__ == s.__name__` (grounding delegates to the shared symbol).\n- [ ] scc on PATH: `scc_loc.analyze(root)` returns an `AnalyzerResult` whose `.loc.max_loc` equals the fixture max. PROVE (integration, skipif scc absent): `pytest -q tests/unit/metrics/test_scc_loc.py::test_live_scc -m integration`.\n- [ ] scc ABSENT (monkeypatched runner raising FileNotFoundError): returns `Unavailable(reason, accruing_since=_ACCRUING_SINCE)`, NOT zeros, NOT a raise. PROVE: `pytest -q tests/unit/metrics/test_scc_loc.py::test_absent_scc_unavailable`.\n\n## Dependencies: 3b30, 9597, e7a0 (recorded depends_on edges).\n## Files: src/rebar/metrics/analyzers/scc_loc.py (new), src/rebar/metrics/analyzers/_scc.py (new), src/rebar/grounding/engine_b_backends.py (delegate to shared), tests/unit/metrics/test_scc_loc.py (new)\n## Scope: M\n\n## Plan corrections (round 4 — supersede any conflicting text above)\n- SHARED SYMBOL (COH/E1, G6): the extracted scc JSON parser is canonically named `parse_scc_json`, in `analyzers/_scc.py`. Signature: `parse_scc_json(scc_json: dict) -> dict` returning `{\"<path>\": <loc:int>, ..., \"max_loc\": <int>}` (per-file LOC + max). `engine_b_backends` re-exports it under the existing name via a direct alias `from rebar.metrics.analyzers._scc import parse_scc_json as _scc_files`. The analyzer LOC contract this adapter feeds is `AnalyzerResult [rebar:3b30-2168-ba16-41fc]`.loc.\n- AC2 (revised proving command, replaces the earlier one): `pytest -q tests/unit/metrics/test_scc_loc.py::test_single_parser_reused` asserting `engine_b_backends._scc_files.__module__ == \"rebar.metrics.analyzers._scc\"` (proves delegation to the shared symbol, not a re-implementation)."}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1784596674827072001,"uuid":"005c2ac7-824b-4141-a924-03445030dccd"}